# Canonical file header

Copy this JSDoc block to the **first lines** of every new or substantially edited `.ts` / `.tsx` file. Adjust placeholders; keep tags consistent so tooling and reviewers can scan quickly.

```ts
/**
 * @file <filename>
 * @module <feature-or-package-name>
 * @description <one-line purpose>
 * @author BharatERP
 * @created YYYY-MM-DD
 * @updated YYYY-MM-DD
 *
 * Notes:
 * - <optional: behavior, side-effects, or "read X before Y">
 */
```

**Rules**

- `@file` — same as the filename (e.g. `stock.service.ts`).
- `@module` — Nest feature (`stock`, `market-data`) or app area (`admin-dashboard`).
- `@updated` — set when behavior or public API changes; omit only if unchanged since `@created`.
- **Do not** use a second competing header format (this template supersedes older `File:` / `Purpose:` only blocks).

For **React components** in `apps/`, `@description` should mention UI role and main props or data source in one line.
